# Story generator in python
"""
'random' module shown in previous project i.e. password generator can also be used to generate random stories.
Program will be such that everytime we will produce a new story. Initially we will store the part of the stories in lists.
These parts/elements in the lists may be changed as per your story. Then we will take the help of random module to accomplish our task.
"""

import random
when = ['A few years ago', 'Yesterday', 'Last night', 'A long time ago','On 20th Jan']
who = ['a rabbit', 'an elephant', 'a mouse', 'a turtle','a cat','iron man']
name = ['Ali', 'Miriam','daniel', 'Hoouk', 'Starwalker','ethan hunt']
residence = ['Barcelona','India', 'Germany', 'Venice', 'England']
went = ['cinema', 'university','seminar', 'school', 'laundry','jungle']
happened = ['made a lot of friends','Eats a burger', 'found a secret key', 'solved a mistery', 'wrote a book','killed thynos']
print(random.choice(when) + ', ' + random.choice(who) + ' that lived in ' + random.choice(residence) + ', went to the ' + random.choice(went) + ' and ' + random.choice(happened))

# O/P
# A few years ago, iron man that lived in Germany, went to the cinema and wrote a book.
